title: Viera girls, boys advance to state golf
text:
Viera girls, boys advance to state golf Brian McCallum , FLORIDA TODAY 8:57 p.m. EDT October 20, 2015 Sophie Liu of Viera putts during Thursday's match against Heritage at Baytree National. (Photo: Craig Bailey/FLORIDA TODAY) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Viera High's boys and girls golf teams qualified Tuesday for next week's state competition, both placing highly in Class 3A regional competition. 
The Hawks girls won their district tournament by a shot over Jupiter. Both the boys and girls played their Region 6-3A events in Vero Beach. Viera's boys placed second behind host Vero Beach. 
Sophie Liu placed third individually for Viera's defending state champion girls team, shooting a 77. Samantha Brimhall was a stroke back at 78 and Taylor Rajeski one more behind at 79. Dayna Owens turned in an 86. 
The tournament was played in windy conditions. 
"It was tough out there," girls coach Greg Ford said. "It affected everything, from putting to drives. For the most part, I think we handled it pretty well." 
The Viera boys were four shots behind the Indians. Calvin Sierota shot a 72. Melbourne's Chase Cutshall qualified for the state tournament as an individual.
